oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Bovine Embryo Transfer and the Veterinary Practitioner
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Elsden, R.P.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Ovum Recovery Techniques
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Once embryo transfer techniques become familiar to the veterinary practitioner, embryos can be efficiently collected from four to five donors and transferred nonsurgically into recipients in less than half a day provided excellent facilities are available. However, considerable initial effort is required to learn the techniques of recovery, recognition, manipulation, and transfer of embryos. It usually takes a full year for an experienced bovine practitioner to become proficient in the technique of embryo transfer.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1981; 49-52
